  "body": "When debugging #8327, I found the output of 'kubectl get pods' was misleading,\n\n```\nPOD        IP           CONTAINER(S)   IMAGE(S)                HOST                                     LABELS      STATUS    CREATED         MESSAGE\nblog-pod   10.244.2.4                                          kubernetes-minion-xft8/130.211.122.180   name=blog   Running   About an hour\n                        nginx          nginx                                                                        Running   About an hour\n                        hugo           caesarxuchao/hugo                                                            Running   About an hour\n                        git-sync       caesarxuchao/git-sync                                                        Running   9 seconds       last termination: exit code 0\n```\n\nThe status of the pod was reported as `Running`, but a further `kubectl get pods -o yaml` suggested the pod was not ready:\n\n```\n...\nstatus:\n    Condition:\n    - status: \"False\"\n      type: Ready\n```\n\n`kubectl get pods` shall warn the user about the fact that the pod is not ready.\n\n@bgrant0607 @nikhiljindal @lavalamp \n",
